The contradiction lies between Lotta's testimony that her camera was set up to take pictures of a meteor shower and the evidence describing her camera. The camera was actually set to automatically take a picture when it detected a loud noise, not specifically for photographing shooting stars or meteor showers.

Therefore, the contradiction is between Evidence 2 (Lotta's Camera) and Testimony 3 (The camera was set up to take pictures of a meteor shower).

